33. paganum: a countryman (from pagus) is here contrasted with armati, and means a civilian. It is often used in this sense after the time of Augustus ; cf. Plin. Ep. ad Tr. 86. zetmilites et pagani ; Tac. Hisl. l. 53 inter paganos corruptior miles.

34. pudorem. honor.
